sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: GvpA and GvpC in J61002 Vector
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: All parts are in the 2014 distribution.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part contains GvpA with a strong RBS, B0034, and GvpC with a medium RBS, B0032. Both of which are under a constitutive promoter, J23100. This construct is in J61002.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Beth Greig

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Weak1 RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-2" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K737016
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: This part conteins gvpA protein's coding sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part conteins gvpA protein's coding sequence. This gene from Planktothrix rubescens can be succesfully expressed in E. coli. The gvpA's expression have been examined by another part " J23106+B0034+gvpA+B0015". (Since it was ligated on cloning vector pSB4A5, we didn't register this part. The gvpA protein conteins a typical domain of the superfamily 'Gas vesicle'(NCBI CDD cl02594). This gene is quiet conserved in most gvp's polycistron. According to Anthony E. Walsby's research, gas vesicles have a similar morphology. GvpA protein is a kind of small hydrophobic protein which forms the ribs of the main structure. 'All cyanobacterial gas vesicles so far analyzed contain a protein (GvpA) of about 7.4 kDa that forms the main mass of the structure and must be responsible for many of its properties.' (Gas Vesicles. Microbiological Reviews. A. E. Walsby)
